 politicized by the temper of the times, the movies they made were often more challenging than before. Thus, just when it might have faded out, Hollywood was reborn--but what was the nature of this rebirth? Hollywood Reborn examines this question, with contributors focusing on many of the era's key figures--noteworthy actors such as Jane Fonda, Al Pacino, Faye Dunaway, and Warren Beatty, and unexpected artists, among them Donald Sutherland, Shelley Winters, and Divine. Each essay offers new perspectives through the lens of an important star, illuminating in the process some of the most fascinating and provocative films of the decade.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aMovie Stars, 1970s, Jane Fonda, Al Pacino, Faye Dunaway, Warren Beatty, Donald Sutherland, Shelley Winters, Divine.1 aCagle, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCagle, Chris.1 aDavis, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Nick.1 aErb, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErb, Cynthia.1 aMorrison, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorrison, James, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorrison, James.1 aPramaggiore, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPramaggiore, Maria.1 aSchoonover, Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchoonover, Karl.1 aSchur, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchur, Thomas.1 aWager, Jans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWager, Jans.1 aWalton, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalton, Jean.1 aWlodarz, Joe, 